      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MISS JECKELL (1) goes very well this trip starting five times for two wins and two minors. In the money last time at this track (34.79) in a Grade 4/5, finishing a 3.5 lengths third. Looks suited here and rates on top. OPALITE (5) has missed the frame at her last two but did run well three back when second (28.77) in a Grade 5 at Sale. Well placed here and should do much better. APPLE ROSE (2) was among the minors three back at Warragul then missed the frame the last two, but drawn box 2 this time where she has two wins. Expected to do much better this time. DARK MIRACLE (8) comes here off a freshen-up and is worth consideration.",
